{% schema %}
{
  "name": "Pillars Grid",
  "class": "section-pillars",
  "settings": [
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "eyebrow",
      "label": "Eyebrow",
      "default": "The Three Pillars"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "headline",
      "label": "Headline",
      "default": "Engineered for Execution, Not Browsing"
    },
    {
      "type": "textarea",
      "id": "subhead",
      "label": "Subheadline",
      "default": "Approach this manual not as a travel blog, but as a strict compliance checklist for your family's relocation pipeline."
    }
  ]
}
{% endschema %}

<style>
  .section-pillars {
    background: #fcfdfd;
    padding: 6rem 2rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #e6e8ea;
  }

  .pillars-header {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto 4rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .pillars-eyebrow {
    font-size: 8.5px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.32em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: rgba(26,95,122,0.7);
    margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
  }

  .pillars-headline {
    font-family: Georgia, 'Times New Roman', serif;
    font-size: clamp(28px, 3.5vw, 40px);
    font-weight: 700;
    line-height: 1.15;
    color: #1a5f7a;
    margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
  }

  .pillars-rule {
    width: 56px;
    height: 2px;
    background: #8bc34a;
    margin: 0 auto 1.5rem;
  }

  .pillars-subhead {
    font-family: Georgia, 'Times New Roman', serif;
    font-size: 15px;
    font-style: italic;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: rgba(26,95,122,0.75);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .pillars-grid {
    max-width: 1200px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 1px;
    background: #e6e8ea;
    border: 1px solid #e6e8ea;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .pillar-card {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    background: #fff;
    padding: 2.5rem;
  }

  .pillar-number-row {
    display: flex;
    align-items: baseline;
    gap: 12px;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .pillar-number {
    font-family: Georgia, 'Times New Roman', serif;
    font-size: 40px;
    font-weight: 700;
    line-height: 1;
    color: #8bc34a;
  }

  .pillar-label {
    font-size: 10px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.28em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: rgba(26,95,122,0.6);
  }

  .pillar-title {
    font-family: Georgia, 'Times New Roman', serif;
    font-size: 22px;
    font-weight: 700;
    line-height: 1.2;
    color: #1a5f7a;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
  }

  .pillar-rule {
    width: 40px;
    height: 2px;
    background: rgba(26,95,122,0.2);
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .pillar-body {
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: rgba(26,95,122,0.8);
    text-align: justify;
    margin: 0;
  }

  @media (max-width: 860px) {
    .pillars-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>

<section class="section-pillars" id="pillars">
  <div class="pillars-header">
    <p class="pillars-eyebrow">{{ section.settings.eyebrow }}</p>
    <h2 class="pillars-headline">{{ section.settings.headline | escape }}</h2>
    <div class="pillars-rule"></div>
    <p class="pillars-subhead">{{ section.settings.subhead }}</p>
  </div>

  <div class="pillars-grid">

    <article class="pillar-card">
      <div class="pillar-number-row">
        <span class="pillar-number">01</span>
        <span class="pillar-label">· Pillar</span>
      </div>
      <h3 class="pillar-title">Healthcare Brackets</h3>
      <div class="pillar-rule"></div>
      <p class="pillar-body">If you are a registered nurse or midwife, the global shortage math is in your favor. This blueprint breaks down the precise healthcare priority visa draws clearing at historically low thresholds, streamlined cross-border CUSMA work passes, and parallel timelines to execute credential recognition and licensing simultaneously.</p>
    </article>

    <article class="pillar-card">
      <div class="pillar-number-row">
        <span class="pillar-number">02</span>
        <span class="pillar-label">· Pillar</span>
      </div>
      <h3 class="pillar-title">Technical Trades</h3>
      <div class="pillar-rule"></div>
      <p class="pillar-body">Built for electricians, plumbers, carpenters, and advanced welders looking to translate their local credentials into international leverage. Map your training history directly to national qualification gates — including the Canadian Red Seal standard, Australian TRA skills assessments, and Germany's Opportunity Card framework.</p>
    </article>

    <article class="pillar-card">
      <div class="pillar-number-row">
        <span class="pillar-number">03</span>
        <span class="pillar-label">· Pillar</span>
      </div>
      <h3 class="pillar-title">Jurisdictional Compliance</h3>
      <div class="pillar-rule"></div>
      <p class="pillar-body">A cross-cutting operational framework for relocating families. Bypasses lifestyle blogs to manage the real-world logistics that make or break a move: localized international driving license reciprocity tiers, portable curriculum mapping (IB/American standard), and 2026 container shipping lane cost dynamics.</p>
    </article>

  </div>
</section>
